The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Selectors to meet in Duesseldorf
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: In a first of its kind, the national hockey selectors will be assembling overseas (Duesseldorf) next month to choose the 16-member Indian squad for the Athens Olympics. Well be meeting in Duesseldorf during the four-nation meet there (July 16-18) to pick the final 16 for Athens, said city-based former Olympian Gurbux Singh, a member of the selection committee. The decision to finalise the squad overseas was taken earlier the question was whether it would be in Amstelveen (where India are currently engaged in a four-nation meet) or Duesseldorf. Since the Amstelveen meet is being telecast live, the IHF has settled for Duesseldorf where wed be watching the games before making the selection, explained Gurbux. The other members of the selection committee are B.P. Govinda, Aslam Sher Khan, S.S. Sodhi, besides IHF president K.P.S. Gill and secretary K. Jyothikumaran. Another former Olympian, M.P. Ganesh, is likely to complete the team as a government nominee.  According to Jyothikumaran, the Indian team will return home for a few days after the Amstelveen meet before leaving again for Duessseldorf.  Copyright 
